The article is a proclamation issued by President Donald Trump declaring January 2021 as National Slavery and Human Trafficking Prevention Month. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of combating human trafficking, which is referred to as "modern slavery," and highlights the efforts of the United States government in addressing this issue. The proclamation mentions initiatives such as the establishment of the Center for Countering Human Trafficking, the release of a National Action Plan to Combat Human Trafficking, and increased funding for organizations providing support to survivors. The proclamation calls upon various stakeholders, including law enforcement, businesses, faith-based organizations, and individuals, to recognize their roles in ending human trafficking and to observe the month with appropriate programs and activities.